NEW YORK LANDMARKS
About the New York City Landmarks

This map displays Individual, Interior and Scenic Landmarks, as well as Historic Districts in all five boroughs. The map also provides detailed building-by-building information for all buildings and sites within individual landmarks and historic districts. Users can click on designated buildings and sites for designation reports, photos and additional information including construction date, architect and style. Click the legend icon on the left of the map screen to identify properties that are color-coded by Landmark type.

New York City comprises 5 boroughs sitting where the Hudson River meets the Atlantic Ocean. At its core is Manhattan, a densely populated borough thats among the worlds major commercial, financial and cultural centers. Its iconic sites include skyscrapers such as the Empire State Building and sprawling Central Park. Broadway theater is staged in neon-lit Times Square.
